1
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,776
When two new recruits
are assigned to the same station,

2
00:00:10,276 --> 00:00:12,878
one is supposed to be brilliant
and the other underachiever.

3
00:00:12,879 --> 00:00:16,248
YOYOGI NISHI POLICE STATION
2012

4
00:00:16,249 --> 00:00:17,450
So which one of you is which?

5
00:00:19,452 --> 00:00:20,987
I think I'm the underachiever.

6
00:00:22,889 --> 00:00:24,991
It's not exactly something to brag about.

7
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,561
I'm so happy to work with you.

8
00:00:34,834 --> 00:00:36,702
How did you get so drunk so fast?

9
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:37,736
I have no idea.

10
00:00:37,737 --> 00:00:39,205
Park your butt right here.

11
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,141
I'm sorry.

12
00:00:43,009 --> 00:00:44,244
Why don't you lie down?

13
00:00:47,113 --> 00:00:48,280
And have some tea.

14
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:49,582
Thanks.

15
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,621
Tell me,

16
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:57,323
why did you join the police force?

17
00:01:00,794 --> 00:01:03,063
I just realized
I never asked you that before.

18
00:01:08,802 --> 00:01:12,338
Well... you don't have to tell me
if you don't want to tell me.

19
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:16,176
There are things about myself
that I don't want to tell others.

20
00:01:20,847 --> 00:01:22,916
I decided to join the police force

21
00:01:24,017 --> 00:01:25,952
because I wanted to belong somewhere.

22
00:01:31,991 --> 00:01:34,227
I want to be able to do well here.

23
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:02,755
<i>Agawa?</i>

24
00:02:04,023 --> 00:02:05,024
You mean, Hiroya Agawa?

25
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,960
Yes.

26
00:02:08,428 --> 00:02:10,262
You should never trust him.

27
00:02:10,263 --> 00:02:12,599
Let's make money together again.

28
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,701
You'll hear from me soon.

29
00:02:15,702 --> 00:02:19,139
If Volunteer makes a move,
Agawa might make a move too.

30
00:02:19,772 --> 00:02:21,508
<i>If you involve Sergeant Koda,</i>

31
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:24,610
I won't forgive you this time.

32
00:02:24,611 --> 00:02:27,147
<i>Please bring Officer Oda
from Kamiazabu Police Station.</i>

33
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,281
I will talk to Officer Oda.

34
00:02:29,282 --> 00:02:30,450
Oda is...

35
00:02:31,084 --> 00:02:32,085
He's dead.

36
00:02:32,652 --> 00:02:33,719
<i>So now you know.</i>

37
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:38,091
<i>You now understand why Arikino
always keeps people at a distance.</i>

38
00:02:38,591 --> 00:02:40,693
There's something
I want to know more than anything.

39
00:02:41,694 --> 00:02:43,296
I want to know why you're pretending

40
00:02:44,364 --> 00:02:46,966
that you're the one
who leaked the information.

41
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:51,803
You want to know what happened

42
00:02:51,804 --> 00:02:54,908
between Satoru, Arikino,
and the man named Agawa, right?

43
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:07,320
Try this place.

44
00:03:13,459 --> 00:03:14,327
What's there?

45
00:03:15,461 --> 00:03:17,330
My old acquaintance is there.

46
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:23,403
MISUZU IMURA
LAWYER

47
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:28,006
I'm sorry I'm running here and there.

48
00:03:28,007 --> 00:03:28,908
It's all right.

49
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:33,445
I got a call from Baijie
on my way back from immigration.

50
00:03:33,446 --> 00:03:34,614
He asked me to see you.

51
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:38,518
Imura-sensei, I'm sorry to trouble you
during your busy schedule.

52
00:03:39,018 --> 00:03:42,088
Please, don't call me "sensei."

53
00:03:44,657 --> 00:03:46,426
Then, allow me to call you Ms. Imura.

54
00:03:49,095 --> 00:03:50,730
About what happened four years ago?

55
00:03:52,165 --> 00:03:53,799
Someone requested

56
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,868
the questioning report
to be disclosed during trial.

57
00:03:56,869 --> 00:03:58,738
I heard that it was you who requested it.

58
00:04:06,112 --> 00:04:08,748
Is it true that you're partners
with that Agawa?

59
00:04:14,787 --> 00:04:15,922
I'll take that as a "yes."

60
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:19,826
Then, it could pose a risk for me.

61
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:23,196
To protect my clients,
I can't discuss it with you.

62
00:04:25,965 --> 00:04:28,401
I understand exactly what you mean.

63
00:04:29,369 --> 00:04:30,403
But still...

64
00:04:31,904 --> 00:04:35,575
I don't think
it's unrelated to that incident,

65
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:40,947
but a Chinese woman was murdered recently.

66
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:43,316
What?

67
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:47,654
<i>We can't allow anyone else's life
to be threatened.</i>

68
00:04:49,656 --> 00:04:50,489
MARI KODA

69
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:52,492
<i>That's why I want to know.</i>

70
00:04:53,259 --> 00:04:56,129
I want to know exactly
what happened four years ago.

71
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:01,367
Please tell me.

72
00:05:02,669 --> 00:05:04,103
Any information would do.

73
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:09,976
Could you please tell me what you know?

74
00:05:20,887 --> 00:05:23,956
The foreign residents I've met in Japan

75
00:05:24,757 --> 00:05:27,894
are doing their best
to be "good" citizens.

76
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:31,597
That alone brings tension to their lives.

77
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,400
Otherwise, they're easily suspected.

78
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:36,669
They are deeply hurt

79
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:40,273
by discrimination based solely
on their skin color or language.

80
00:05:41,407 --> 00:05:43,443
Some have even lost their lives.

81
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,314
As for me...

82
00:05:49,482 --> 00:05:50,917
As lawyers, it's our duty

83
00:05:51,684 --> 00:05:54,921
to give voice to these individuals' words
and heartfelt sentiments.

84
00:05:57,390 --> 00:06:00,059
At least, I believe
it's my responsibility.

85
00:06:25,418 --> 00:06:26,919
I'm not really supposed to,

86
00:06:27,787 --> 00:06:30,089
but I'm putting myself at risk
to show you something.

87
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:38,030
This is an internal report
from within the Tokyo Metropolitan PD.

88
00:06:38,931 --> 00:06:41,434
I obtained this confidentially
after the trial.

89
00:06:43,469 --> 00:06:46,138
A third party has reviewed
Agawa's questioning session,

90
00:06:46,139 --> 00:06:47,740
which was filmed in secret.

91
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:53,880
The report concluded

92
00:06:55,114 --> 00:06:59,585
that the series of misinterpretations
appeared to be intentional.

93
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:16,601
PERSON UNDER REVIEW:
LIEUTENANT HIROYA AGAWA

94
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:18,937
TO VERIFY THE CONSISTENCY

95
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:22,607
BETWEEN THE SUSPECT'S STATEMENT
AND THE INTERPRETATION

96
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:26,312
THE STATEMENT APPEARS TO HAVE BEEN
MISINTERPRETED INTENTIONALLY

97
00:07:29,649 --> 00:07:32,484
REVIEW DETAILS

98
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:33,952
LI HONGFEI'S INTERVIEW RECORDS

99
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,320
SOMEONE ELSE TAKES CARE OF SELLING
THE PRODUCT

100
00:07:35,321 --> 00:07:36,521
SO, I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING

101
00:07:36,522 --> 00:07:37,689
I'LL BE KILLED IF I TELL THE POLICE
ABOUT THE BOSS

102
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:38,824
YOU KNOW THE BOSS, DON'T YOU?
I'LL REWARD YOU PROPERLY

103
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:39,724
SO FRAME ANOTHER FELLOW COUNTRYMAN
AS THE BOSS

104
00:07:39,725 --> 00:07:43,629
Do you know who compiled
this detailed report?

105
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:45,731
I don't know.

106
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,902
However, I can say that anyone
capable of handling this level

107
00:07:50,903 --> 00:07:52,472
of verification must be an expert.

108
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:56,576
For example, a Chinese interpreter
for the Tokyo Metropolitan PD.

109
00:08:02,748 --> 00:08:05,651
Please stop digging into my past.

110
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,721
I beg you.

111
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,702
So, this internal information was...

112
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:28,574
Who provided you
with this internal information?

113
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:32,411
Let me clarify.

114
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:36,514
Are you basically asking me

115
00:08:36,515 --> 00:08:39,151
who leaked
this misinterpretation issue outside?

116
00:08:43,756 --> 00:08:46,926
It was Satoru Oda, wasn't it?

117
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:57,335
INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION
KAMIAZABU POLICE STATION, 2020

118
00:08:57,336 --> 00:08:58,371
Detective Agawa,

119
00:08:59,205 --> 00:09:01,374
have you finished questioning Lin Mengqi?

120
00:09:02,275 --> 00:09:04,543
Yeah. I think it's good.

121
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,778
She's being released tomorrow.

122
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,847
What? Why are you releasing her?

123
00:09:08,347 --> 00:09:11,550
She co-manages the illegal
adult entertainment outlet, right?

124
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:14,120
She was only introducing escorts.

125
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:16,389
But still...

126
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:19,859
Keeping her here any longer
would just be a waste of our time.

127
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:26,232
And I don't think we need to charge
the other escort women either.

128
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,744
You know these two, don't you?

129
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:41,847
Excuse me, can I disturb you for a moment?

130
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:43,949
Yes?

131
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,952
Detective Agawa has asked me to follow up.

132
00:09:46,452 --> 00:09:47,687
I'll be done in a minute.

133
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,291
All right, go ahead.

134
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:57,196
It seems that your spouse visa
is about to expire

135
00:09:57,697 --> 00:10:00,166
because you got divorced
from your husband.

136
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:02,768
Screw you.

137
00:10:05,871 --> 00:10:08,074
You should find a job quickly.

138
00:10:08,908 --> 00:10:09,942
A different kind of job.

139
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:13,578
That way, you'll be able to secure
your residency status.

140
00:10:13,579 --> 00:10:16,849
Don't act like it's that simple.
You don't know anything.

141
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:18,951
You need to make up your mind first

142
00:10:19,819 --> 00:10:21,019
that you are starting over today.

143
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:25,057
Shut your mouth!
It's none of your business.

144
00:10:28,661 --> 00:10:30,162
If you can make that decision,

145
00:10:31,697 --> 00:10:33,933
your life can have a fresh start.

146
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:43,476
That's what happened with me.

147
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,888
The International Division
of Higashi Shinjuku Police Station

148
00:10:56,889 --> 00:10:59,225
seems to have their hands full
with the murder case.

149
00:11:00,092 --> 00:11:04,063
I bet Miss Koda could use your help.

150
00:11:05,931 --> 00:11:07,366
I doubt that.

151
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:15,006
But you should rely on Miss Koda

152
00:11:15,007 --> 00:11:16,409
every once in a while.

153
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:25,317
What did you just say?

154
00:11:27,286 --> 00:11:29,588
It means we all depend on each other.

155
00:11:31,957 --> 00:11:33,092
Thanks.

156
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,185
Hello, Mr. Agawa.

157
00:12:00,486 --> 00:12:02,555
I was so thrilled to hear from you.

158
00:12:04,457 --> 00:12:05,891
Come on, get in.

159
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:35,121
So, is this your safehouse?

160
00:12:35,988 --> 00:12:38,858
No, it's not.
We just happened to be here today.

161
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:44,497
It feels like a homecoming to me.

162
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:46,231
Then, I should say,

163
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:48,434
"Welcome home."

164
00:12:49,368 --> 00:12:51,971
How's your business going?
Are you making any money?

165
00:12:52,538 --> 00:12:55,106
Yep. I've started making
fake Residence Cards

166
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:56,776
for illegal residents as well.

167
00:12:57,476 --> 00:12:59,945
If you find anyone who needs them,
send them to me.

168
00:13:00,546 --> 00:13:02,581
I'll put them to work in rural factories.

169
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:07,553
When's your next meeting?

170
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:12,258
I'd love to come this time
since it's been a while.

171
00:13:12,758 --> 00:13:13,959
I'm open to discussing business.

172
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:17,596
Then, can I confirm if you really mean it?

173
00:13:49,628 --> 00:13:52,665
Please, forgive me.
I beg you, don't kill me.

174
00:13:54,466 --> 00:13:56,869
Hey, you're going to end up killing him.

175
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:03,275
He's so stupid that he tried
to snitch on us to the police.

176
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:06,078
You wouldn't do that, would you?

177
00:14:10,616 --> 00:14:12,518
Help me.

178
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,587
I don't want to die.

179
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,525
Help me.

180
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:25,898
It's been a while, you know.

181
00:14:27,099 --> 00:14:28,634
So, I just want to double-check.

182
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:35,608
I'm so relieved you haven't changed.

183
00:15:12,211 --> 00:15:14,813
- Excuse me, ma'am.
- Yes?

184
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:18,350
Can I speak with you for a moment
about Lin Mengqi?

185
00:15:19,718 --> 00:15:20,753
Sure.

186
00:15:21,287 --> 00:15:23,688
She seemed to be working very hard, but...

187
00:15:23,689 --> 00:15:24,656
SEICHO CHEMICALS

188
00:15:24,657 --> 00:15:26,625
<i>Why are you poking around
about Lin Mengqi?</i>

189
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:31,062
I'm not investigating the Lin Mengqi case.

190
00:15:31,063 --> 00:15:32,298
Then, what are you doing?

191
00:15:32,798 --> 00:15:33,632
Um, I am...

192
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:38,938
Whatever it is,

193
00:15:40,005 --> 00:15:42,007
we're the ones handling the murder case.

194
00:15:42,508 --> 00:15:43,509
Understood?

195
00:15:52,718 --> 00:15:54,086
Listen, Koda.

196
00:15:54,753 --> 00:15:55,654
Yes?

197
00:15:57,289 --> 00:16:00,158
I understand you want to find the killer

198
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:02,628
since you knew the victim.

199
00:16:03,696 --> 00:16:06,465
But you're not part
of the investigation team.

200
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,034
Carelessly contacting a person of interest

201
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:12,438
could jeopardize the investigation.
You know that, right?

202
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,188
Look at this.

203
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:30,723
Okay.

204
00:16:34,259 --> 00:16:35,694
It was caught on a security camera.

205
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:41,867
This is footage of Lin Mengqi
right before she was killed.

206
00:16:44,636 --> 00:16:46,638
We can't make out this person's face.

207
00:16:48,774 --> 00:16:49,675
Now...

208
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:52,778
I'm asking you this personally.

209
00:16:55,614 --> 00:16:58,817
What theory did you draw
from your investigation?

210
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:06,725
I found out

211
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:10,195
what Lin Mengqi used to tell
her colleague.

212
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:13,132
"I'm safe.

213
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:16,468
<i>I'll never get caught by the police.</i>

214
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:18,737
<i>They won't catch me</i>

215
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:23,342
because I have something on the police."

216
00:17:24,810 --> 00:17:25,811
"Something on the police?"

217
00:17:27,479 --> 00:17:29,882
I don't know exactly
what that was, though.

218
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:32,851
And that

219
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:36,889
appears to be her point of contact
with Volunteer.

220
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:54,706
What are you doing,

221
00:17:55,674 --> 00:17:56,675
Greenhead?

222
00:17:58,644 --> 00:17:59,812
Lieutenant...

223
00:18:11,356 --> 00:18:15,327
So, you think the police
and Volunteer are connected...

224
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:18,797
Yes.

225
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,568
What's the basis?

226
00:18:27,539 --> 00:18:28,640
Well...

227
00:18:42,354 --> 00:18:43,622
Think about pigeons.

228
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:47,593
Pigeons are a symbol of peace, right?

229
00:18:49,394 --> 00:18:50,395
Excuse me?

230
00:18:53,198 --> 00:18:54,633
Pigeons can also be aggressive.

231
00:18:55,434 --> 00:18:58,470
When they see pigeons
smaller than themselves,

232
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,239
they attack them.

233
00:19:04,443 --> 00:19:08,714
But people still want to see them
as a symbol of peace.

234
00:19:16,088 --> 00:19:18,423
We just draw our own one-sided conclusion

235
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,759
and choose to be at peace.

236
00:19:25,364 --> 00:19:26,665
But by doing that,

237
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:30,369
we might end up overlooking the truth.

238
00:19:38,810 --> 00:19:39,778
Can I dare

239
00:19:43,615 --> 00:19:45,450
to draw my own one-sided conclusion?

240
00:19:49,621 --> 00:19:50,722
Lieutenant...

241
00:19:53,225 --> 00:19:57,729
Are you planning to do
something by any chance?

242
00:20:03,802 --> 00:20:04,803
What makes you think that?

243
00:20:07,239 --> 00:20:08,607
I have no concrete grounds.

244
00:20:11,109 --> 00:20:14,246
It's just a hunch as a detective.

245
00:20:20,018 --> 00:20:21,486
You're pretty amusing.

246
00:20:25,123 --> 00:20:26,358
You're overthinking it,

247
00:20:27,659 --> 00:20:28,660
Greenhead.

248
00:20:41,473 --> 00:20:43,575
You know the misinterpretation incident.

249
00:20:45,811 --> 00:20:48,447
It was Sergeant Oda
who leaked it to the press,

250
00:20:50,616 --> 00:20:51,917
wasn't it?

251
00:20:59,057 --> 00:21:00,792
Do you know Toyozumi at the TMPD?

252
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:05,029
You mean the officer in Internal Affairs?

253
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:08,967
It's just a rumor, but they say
your career is over if he targets you.

254
00:21:11,903 --> 00:21:16,108
Satoru and I used to get into trouble
and get caught by him all the time.

255
00:21:18,543 --> 00:21:22,381
2009

256
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:29,954
- Hey!
- Hey, Satoru.

257
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:30,855
You're late!

258
00:21:30,856 --> 00:21:32,290
- Come, sit down over here.
- Sit.

259
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:33,357
- Come on.
- Have a drink.

260
00:21:33,358 --> 00:21:34,992
- You're feeling generous today.
- I am.

261
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:36,560
I'm loaded, you know.

262
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:37,528
What did you do?

263
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:39,897
Three freakin' motorcycles!

264
00:21:39,898 --> 00:21:41,565
- From where?
- Behind the station.

265
00:21:41,566 --> 00:21:43,502
How much did you get for them in total?

266
00:21:44,002 --> 00:21:45,003
800,000 yen.

267
00:21:46,772 --> 00:21:47,972
Are you kidding me?

268
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:49,408
That's so awesome!

269
00:21:51,243 --> 00:21:52,577
But have you told Kaneko and the others?

270
00:21:53,078 --> 00:21:54,745
- Of course not.
- Of course not.

271
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:55,881
If I did, they'd take all the money.

272
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:07,092
The police came to me
because of you idiots.

273
00:22:08,193 --> 00:22:10,028
They thought I stole the bikes.

274
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:15,901
How are you going to fix this?

275
00:22:18,136 --> 00:22:19,438
I'm so sorry...

276
00:22:20,939 --> 00:22:22,140
Wait, Kaneko.

277
00:22:22,974 --> 00:22:25,110
Satoru had nothing to do with it.

278
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:28,546
Don't give me some cheap act

279
00:22:28,547 --> 00:22:31,083
of covering for each other
like in some dumb comic book stories.

280
00:22:56,408 --> 00:22:57,475
- Hey!
- Crap!

281
00:22:57,476 --> 00:22:58,876
- Shit!
- Is it you guys again?

282
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:00,112
It's okay. Run.

283
00:23:10,789 --> 00:23:11,923
- Go after them.
- Yes, sir.

284
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:17,328
How long are you going to keep this up?

285
00:23:17,329 --> 00:23:18,730
How the hell should I know?

286
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:21,666
Listen, you idiot.

287
00:23:23,168 --> 00:23:26,004
You might not think
one bike is a big deal at all.

288
00:23:26,838 --> 00:23:29,975
But if you steal this one,
you won't be able to stop.

289
00:23:33,512 --> 00:23:34,546
Oda...

290
00:23:39,284 --> 00:23:41,052
I'd hate to see you go down that path.

291
00:23:43,889 --> 00:23:44,956
Remember one thing.

292
00:23:46,992 --> 00:23:50,362
Whether you can get back
on the right track or not

293
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:53,265
is entirely up to you.

294
00:23:58,537 --> 00:23:59,370
<i>Before we knew it,</i>

295
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:02,641
he was influenced by Toyozumi
and joined the police.

296
00:24:06,378 --> 00:24:09,481
About three months after Satoru
became partners with Agawa,

297
00:24:11,082 --> 00:24:13,150
<i>he was approached by Toyozumi.</i>

298
00:24:13,151 --> 00:24:15,153
<i>And he was unusually worked up about it.</i>

299
00:24:17,489 --> 00:24:21,292
I looked into the questioning sessions
Hiroya Agawa has been involved in.

300
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:22,259
2021

301
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:25,296
Compared to those conducted
by other investigators,

302
00:24:25,297 --> 00:24:28,700
his sessions were often unrecorded
or not videotaped.

303
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:32,771
I bet you know what I'm talking about,
being his partner.

304
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:38,776
In explaining the reason,

305
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:42,547
he says it was because the suspects
didn't want the sessions recorded.

306
00:24:46,785 --> 00:24:50,989
But have you ever questioned
his skills as an interpreter?

307
00:24:55,026 --> 00:24:56,228
You mean, Detective Agawa

308
00:24:57,095 --> 00:25:00,065
deliberately didn't have
his questioning recorded?

309
00:25:00,765 --> 00:25:03,434
Are you saying he didn't want
any records to be left?

310
00:25:03,435 --> 00:25:04,503
Listen, Oda.

311
00:25:06,171 --> 00:25:09,140
You're the only person I can ask
to do something like this.

312
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,011
I want to have

313
00:25:13,745 --> 00:25:17,549
Agawa's Chinese interpretation
reviewed for accuracy.

314
00:25:19,684 --> 00:25:21,319
What do you mean by "review"?

315
00:25:53,919 --> 00:25:55,286
Mr. Li Hongfei.

316
00:25:55,287 --> 00:25:57,656
I'm Oda from the International
Investigation Division.

317
00:25:58,223 --> 00:26:00,057
This is Detective Agawa.

318
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:02,761
He'll conduct the questioning
and interpret for you.

319
00:26:03,662 --> 00:26:04,862
Mr. Li Hongfei.

320
00:26:04,863 --> 00:26:07,832
He is Oda from the International
Investigation Division.

321
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:09,568
I'm Agawa.

322
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:12,003
I'll conduct the questioning
and interpret for you.

323
00:26:15,974 --> 00:26:19,044
Will you let me know the results
of the review?

324
00:26:24,616 --> 00:26:25,884
It depends on the content.

325
00:26:32,223 --> 00:26:33,325
<i>I can't believe</i>

326
00:26:34,092 --> 00:26:37,228
Internal Affairs would use
an ordinary officer as their spy.

327
00:26:38,697 --> 00:26:40,398
It's totally unheard of.

328
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:43,234
And here's another thought.

329
00:26:44,302 --> 00:26:46,471
Even if he had been ordered to,

330
00:26:46,972 --> 00:26:49,608
I don't think Sergeant Oda
would betray his partner.

331
00:26:54,579 --> 00:26:57,349
Do you think he told Arikeeno
what he had to do?

332
00:26:59,351 --> 00:27:00,852
<i>Satoru probably couldn't tell him</i>

333
00:27:02,554 --> 00:27:04,856
<i>because he cared about him too much.</i>

334
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:10,161
MASHIMA LAUNDRY

335
00:27:48,566 --> 00:27:49,567
What's going on?

336
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:55,807
I've always loved to watch
laundry machines tumble.

337
00:27:58,043 --> 00:28:02,514
It helps me calm down
and sort out my thoughts.

338
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:16,695
Listen, Ryo.

339
00:28:26,004 --> 00:28:30,275
I will always protect you
no matter where I am.

340
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:34,012
I will protect you no matter what.

341
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:40,585
What's gotten into you all of a sudden?

342
00:28:43,822 --> 00:28:44,656
You have my word.

343
00:28:48,993 --> 00:28:49,994
All right.

344
00:28:51,496 --> 00:28:52,664
I'm counting on you, then.

345
00:29:02,207 --> 00:29:04,209
<i>I've reviewed your record.</i>

346
00:29:05,977 --> 00:29:07,812
And Sergeant Arikino,

347
00:29:08,847 --> 00:29:11,916
from what I've heard,
you're fluent in Chinese.

348
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:13,651
That's correct, sir.

349
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:20,224
This, right here, is a video recording

350
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:22,560
of a Chinese suspect's
questioning session.

351
00:29:24,863 --> 00:29:27,198
I'd like to hear your opinion
on its content.

352
00:29:28,633 --> 00:29:29,868
Understood, sir.

353
00:29:35,707 --> 00:29:37,141
<i>Mr. Li Hongfei.</i>

354
00:29:37,142 --> 00:29:39,377
<i>I'm Oda from the International
Investigation Division.</i>

355
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:41,913
<i>This is Detective Agawa.</i>

356
00:29:42,413 --> 00:29:45,250
<i>He'll conduct the questioning
and interpret for you.</i>

357
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,034
How was it?

358
00:30:03,668 --> 00:30:06,337
There were some parts
I just couldn't overlook.

359
00:30:09,841 --> 00:30:14,412
Lieutenant Agawa asked the suspect
who instructed him to steal.

360
00:30:14,913 --> 00:30:16,347
And here's the suspect's response.

361
00:30:18,383 --> 00:30:20,985
"I'll be killed if I tell the police
about the boss."

362
00:30:22,353 --> 00:30:23,922
"You know the boss, don't you?"

363
00:30:24,923 --> 00:30:26,257
"I'll reward you properly,

364
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:30,028
so frame another fellow countryman
as the boss."

365
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:31,563
That's what he said.

366
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:36,634
But the interpretation
given by the lieutenant was different.

367
00:30:37,202 --> 00:30:40,605
In response to whether someone
had instructed him to steal, he says...

368
00:30:41,506 --> 00:30:44,375
"Someone else takes care of selling
the product.

369
00:30:44,876 --> 00:30:46,578
So, I don't know anything."

370
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:50,582
It definitely wasn't a mistake.

371
00:30:52,217 --> 00:30:54,719
It's clear he intentionally
twisted the statement.

372
00:30:58,256 --> 00:31:02,193
Go through the conversations
with all the suspects to translate them.

373
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:05,096
And compile a report.

374
00:31:07,065 --> 00:31:07,966
Yes, sir.

375
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:36,594
Satoru...

376
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:45,103
What on earth are you doing?

377
00:31:48,306 --> 00:31:49,874
I see.

378
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:57,215
So, you were the translator chosen
by Superintendent Toyozumi.

379
00:32:00,051 --> 00:32:02,687
Why did you agree to spy
for Internal Affairs?

380
00:32:04,589 --> 00:32:07,392
What do you think would happen
if your colleagues found out

381
00:32:08,693 --> 00:32:10,260
that you betrayed your partner?

382
00:32:10,261 --> 00:32:12,130
How was Agawa's interpretation?

383
00:32:16,801 --> 00:32:19,203
Don't you have to worry
about our colleagues,

384
00:32:21,139 --> 00:32:23,141
given that you did the translation?

385
00:32:26,377 --> 00:32:27,512
What do you mean by that?

386
00:32:31,482 --> 00:32:32,417
You once told me

387
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:37,322
that you wanted to do well at the police.

388
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:40,191
Then, don't let others know.

389
00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:42,961
They should never know

390
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:46,831
that you cooperated with Internal Affairs.

391
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:08,386
Because you always looked so lonely,

392
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:12,390
I wanted to be there for you.

393
00:33:14,092 --> 00:33:16,361
I wanted to walk by your side
to make you laugh

394
00:33:18,396 --> 00:33:20,298
and ease your loneliness.

395
00:33:24,635 --> 00:33:26,270
I want to keep doing that for you.

396
00:33:31,209 --> 00:33:32,210
But...

397
00:33:37,749 --> 00:33:39,584
I guess, I can't be the one.

398
00:33:45,790 --> 00:33:47,091
Someday,

399
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:52,130
someone might help you live in this world
with peace in your heart.

400
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:55,099
If you meet someone
who can do that for you,

401
00:33:58,469 --> 00:34:00,605
promise me
you'll never let go of his hand.

402
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:38,176
I did some more digging.

403
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:42,547
You're partners
with Detective Agawa, right?

404
00:34:44,449 --> 00:34:48,252
You sensed something was off
during the questioning, didn't you?

405
00:34:51,656 --> 00:34:55,560
Questioning sessions are typically
recorded, but Agawa's sessions aren't.

406
00:34:58,563 --> 00:35:00,730
I know that what I'm asking you
is outrageous.

407
00:35:00,731 --> 00:35:02,667
But I really need it.

408
00:35:03,901 --> 00:35:04,902
Sergeant Oda,

409
00:35:05,903 --> 00:35:08,005
are you sure
you don't have any recordings?

410
00:35:14,345 --> 00:35:15,880
Agawa's misinterpretation

411
00:35:16,714 --> 00:35:19,549
caused my clients to be indicted
though they were innocent.

412
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:21,052
They didn't commit the crime,

413
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:24,589
but were falsely convicted.

414
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:27,891
I believe

415
00:35:27,892 --> 00:35:30,795
that's the most detestable offense
that exists in this world.

416
00:35:32,897 --> 00:35:34,297
They were robbed of their lives

417
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:37,668
while they were trying so hard
to start over in this country.

418
00:35:42,273 --> 00:35:47,145
You're the only one who can prove that.

419
00:36:06,731 --> 00:36:07,664
What the...

420
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:11,067
"DELIBERATE MISINTERPRETATION"
DURING POLICE QUESTIONING

421
00:36:11,068 --> 00:36:12,203
How was this article possible?

422
00:36:17,308 --> 00:36:18,442
Hello?

423
00:36:19,944 --> 00:36:20,945
<i>Hi, Ryo.</i>

424
00:36:21,579 --> 00:36:25,583
Are you the one who leaked information
for that article?

425
00:36:29,787 --> 00:36:31,355
What were you thinking?

426
00:36:34,225 --> 00:36:35,092
I'm sorry.

427
00:36:36,961 --> 00:36:39,130
I couldn't think of any other way.

428
00:36:41,566 --> 00:36:42,767
<i>What did you do that for?</i>

429
00:36:45,102 --> 00:36:46,804
I wanted to save those people

430
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:50,241
who have been falsely convicted
in this case.

431
00:36:53,110 --> 00:36:56,681
The illegality of the questioning
must be proven at trial,

432
00:36:57,648 --> 00:37:00,685
but the data isn't admissible
as it was obtained illegally.

433
00:37:02,253 --> 00:37:04,355
I had no choice but to have the media
expose this.

434
00:37:05,056 --> 00:37:06,157
But still,

435
00:37:06,924 --> 00:37:08,793
you know what the consequences will be.

436
00:37:16,467 --> 00:37:17,335
I'm sorry.

437
00:37:18,869 --> 00:37:19,869
I'll call you later.

438
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,973
Satoru, hold on.

439
00:37:34,919 --> 00:37:37,989
How dare you repay my kindness with evil

440
00:37:39,156 --> 00:37:41,092
when I've been so nice to you all along?

441
00:37:45,830 --> 00:37:47,932
I didn't expect you to secretly record it.

442
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:50,868
I'm surprised Internal Affairs
would go that far.

443
00:37:54,171 --> 00:37:56,507
Were you the one
who leaked it to the media?

444
00:37:58,142 --> 00:38:00,378
You're the one who betrayed first,
aren't you?

445
00:38:02,179 --> 00:38:06,717
The article doesn't go into detail
about what you did.

446
00:38:07,852 --> 00:38:09,520
I only gave them the audio recording.

447
00:38:10,521 --> 00:38:11,856
Doesn't that save your skin?

448
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:18,195
Now tell me...

449
00:38:20,831 --> 00:38:23,501
Remember the questioning
of the woman named Lin Mengqi?

450
00:38:24,869 --> 00:38:26,804
Did you record that session as well?

451
00:38:32,543 --> 00:38:34,245
Could you please not give the data

452
00:38:35,413 --> 00:38:37,548
from that session to Internal Affairs?

453
00:38:45,423 --> 00:38:48,326
It's over for both of us, anyway.

454
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:51,395
For me, naturally,

455
00:38:52,363 --> 00:38:56,100
but you won't escape punishment
for leaking the information.

456
00:38:58,069 --> 00:38:59,337
Before we know it,

457
00:39:00,104 --> 00:39:04,408
we'll be identified and exposed
as the culprits behind this mess.

458
00:39:05,409 --> 00:39:06,711
And those in the police

459
00:39:07,945 --> 00:39:10,815
despise those who betray
their fellow officers.

460
00:39:14,352 --> 00:39:15,486
But if you

461
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:20,256
hand over the data
from Lin Mengqi's questioning...

462
00:39:20,257 --> 00:39:21,392
Back then,

463
00:39:22,793 --> 00:39:25,429
what were you discussing with Lin Mengqi?

464
00:39:41,212 --> 00:39:44,448
Because I wanted to hear the truth
directly from you

465
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:47,952
I chose not to release that data.

466
00:39:52,056 --> 00:39:54,125
You were obviously shaken up then.

467
00:39:56,394 --> 00:39:58,229
What did she tell you?

468
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,101
Detective Agawa,

469
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:06,903
please tell me.

470
00:40:06,904 --> 00:40:09,105
If you keep insisting that you're going

471
00:40:09,106 --> 00:40:12,676
to make that data public no matter what...

472
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:36,099
NO ANSWER

473
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:37,568
WHERE ARE YOU?

474
00:40:52,183 --> 00:40:53,117
Hello?

475
00:40:53,918 --> 00:40:56,187
<i>Arikino, where are you now?</i>

476
00:40:57,021 --> 00:40:58,622
I'm at the Kamiazabu Police Station.

477
00:40:59,123 --> 00:41:00,257
What's the matter?

478
00:41:01,525 --> 00:41:03,160
<i>No one has contacted you yet?</i>

479
00:41:04,728 --> 00:41:05,729
What?

480
00:41:07,598 --> 00:41:08,632
<i>Listen.</i>

481
00:41:09,433 --> 00:41:10,835
<i>Don't panic. Just listen.</i>

482
00:41:13,270 --> 00:41:14,238
<i>Oda is...</i>

483
00:41:15,973 --> 00:41:16,941
<i>He's dead.</i>

484
00:41:49,807 --> 00:41:50,875
Hi, Arikeeno.

485
00:41:55,412 --> 00:41:56,614
Arikeeno,

486
00:41:59,049 --> 00:42:00,251
what's wrong?

487
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:04,722
You know what?

488
00:42:07,591 --> 00:42:09,193
I was in a relationship with Oda.

489
00:42:13,831 --> 00:42:14,765
I couldn't...

490
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:18,969
I couldn't save him.

491
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:22,673
He was...

492
00:42:23,173 --> 00:42:25,109
He was such a fool.

493
00:42:28,879 --> 00:42:30,981
He was so honest and sincere

494
00:42:34,752 --> 00:42:37,187
that I should have protected him.

495
00:42:46,163 --> 00:42:48,365
Arikeeno, you don't have to tell me

496
00:42:50,834 --> 00:42:52,303
if you don't want to tell me.

497
00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:00,711
I've been wanting to tell you,

498
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:05,649
because you're the only one I could.

499
00:43:20,864 --> 00:43:22,166
You know what I think?

500
00:43:22,733 --> 00:43:25,034
<i>Let's say</i>

501
00:43:25,035 --> 00:43:27,571
<i>someone disappears from your sight.</i>

502
00:43:28,772 --> 00:43:32,042
<i>But the person remains
inside all the people left behind.</i>

503
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:33,911
<i>I think...</i>

504
00:43:34,979 --> 00:43:37,047
<i>...pieces of the person remain behind.</i>

505
00:43:38,182 --> 00:43:39,016
Thank you.

506
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:40,818
Agawa!

507
00:43:44,021 --> 00:43:46,255
Wait a minute.
That's not what we agreed on.

508
00:43:46,256 --> 00:43:47,457
Shut the hell up.

509
00:43:47,458 --> 00:43:48,726
I'm going to kill you.

510
00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:57,367
ORIGINAL STORY BY KUROMARU

511
00:43:57,368 --> 00:44:00,269
So, you're making extra money
without telling your buddy?

512
00:44:00,270 --> 00:44:01,438
Don't you dare!

513
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:05,341
Get your hands off me, old man!
You should die!

514
00:44:05,342 --> 00:44:08,011
Yeah, you're right.

515
00:44:08,012 --> 00:44:09,780
But you're following the same fate.

516
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:14,283
Your buddy finding out about this,
and me throwing you into jail

517
00:44:14,284 --> 00:44:16,086
would be like death to you.

518
00:44:17,821 --> 00:44:21,091
But there's one way for you to survive.

519
00:44:25,129 --> 00:44:28,966
Tell me
where Volunteer's meeting place is.
